Rexian Government

The Rexian government is quite simple. At the top of the food chain sits The Rexian Might, who primarily serves as a sort of ruler/dictator for the nation. To acquire the spot of Might, there is no formal election process. Instead, as in the rest of Rexian society, one must take the head of the Might in order to become one themselves. The Might has full control over resource allocation and the military, yet, in a weird phenomena, everyone seems to trust the Might and their word, honoring their immense strength and finding comfort in it.

The Might is protected by 5-10 mages of incredible strength, known as The Mystics, who are there to insure that the trial by combat process remains unharmed. Many times in the youth of the nation, the Might had been ambushed by a large group of people, creating an unfair battle dynamic.

As for legislation, there is no formal written code or law in Rexia, but instead inherent values all Rexian's hold close to them. The main one, is to never harm children or the elderly, unless explicitly challenged.

Finally, where you live in Rexia is entirely dependent on strength as well. Districts are named after animals, reflecting different tiers of strength, with the strongest realm being Mount Hippon, where the Might lives, sitting atop the Undying Fortress. To progress to a wealthier territory, one must commence in combat trials to earn a residency license. The stronger the territory, the more its riches, incentivizing Rexians to grow stronger and hone their combative abilities.
